# Prototype the decision loop on replayed traffic

## Step

Cheapest touchable artifact: a throwaway Fable loop fed a real day of joelclaw message traffic (replayed from the stream/journal, not live), producing what it *would have sent* — rewrites in one voice, storm aggregations, hold/deliver choices with one-line reasons.

This is an alignment instrument, not a cutover gate. Joel ruled out a shadow window; full replacement stands. The prototype exists so Joel can react to the agent's actual judgment and voice before the decision-loop design closes — a reaction beats a discussion.

Standing call (Joel, 2026-07-21): fine with a prototype **as long as it has a clear iteration path to production if it proves out**. So build on the real seams, not a mock rig: replay through the real stream read API (the seam map's paginated replay), package the loop the way the plugin-surface map recommends (Claude plugin), and write decision receipts in the shapes the design will keep. Harness glue and the review surface may be throwaway; the loop core, its tooling, and its prompt files are the seed of the production container. The result section must name the iteration path: what hardens, what gets discarded, what the next slice is.

Joel touches the output (a rendered before/after of a real day) and grills: is the voice right, are the aggregations right, what did it wrongly hold or wrongly deliver.

Resolved when Joel has reacted to at least one full replayed day and the reactions are recorded as design inputs in the result section. Feeds [Design the decision loop](./design-decision-loop.svx) and [Plan the full cutover](./plan-full-cutover.svx).

## Build receipt (2026-07-21)

Built the seed at [`prototypes/agent-comms-gateway/claude-plugin/`](../../../prototypes/agent-comms-gateway/claude-plugin/). This location follows the standing iteration path: the Claude plugin, prompt files, replay contract, and receipt validation can harden in place; only the journal-spool adapter and generated review surface are throwaway edges.

- Replayed the full stored day `2026-07-20` read-only from `~/.joelclaw/spool/message-journal`, the real local journal fallback surface.
- The canonical stream still lacks the seam map's independent paginated time read. The prototype's read-only adapter implements the requested `readSince(recordedAt, limit, cursor)` page shape so production can replace the edge without moving judgment code.
- Read 206 unique journal lifecycle events and selected 100 outbound producer requests. Later lifecycle rows show 97 confirmed deliveries.
- Pi inference (`openai-codex/gpt-5.6-sol`) produced 13 validated decision receipts: 4 deliver, 2 hold, 6 aggregate, and 1 escalate. The six storm receipts cover 93 inputs. Every one of the 100 input event IDs appears exactly once.
- The plugin agent declares the production Fable harness. The replay runner keeps inference behind Pi, as required; it used no paid API key and no OpenRouter.
- Nothing was sent. The runner has no transport tool and the MCP server refuses to start unless `JOELCLAW_GATEWAY_REPLAY_ONLY=1`.
- Raw replay data and the generated review note are mode `0600` and locally excluded through `.git/info/exclude`. They contain private message traffic and must not be committed or published.

Review: [Decision-loop replay review: 2026-07-20](./review-decision-loop-replay-2026-07-20.svx)

Private machine receipts:

- `.brain/data/agent-comms-gateway/replay-2026-07-20/input.json`
- `.brain/data/agent-comms-gateway/replay-2026-07-20/decisions.jsonl`
- `.brain/data/agent-comms-gateway/replay-2026-07-20/summary.json`
- `.brain/data/agent-comms-gateway/replay-2026-07-20/status.json` — check for `state: "complete"` and a matching `runId` before reading the other artifacts.

Regenerate:

```bash
node prototypes/agent-comms-gateway/claude-plugin/scripts/run-replay.mjs --day 2026-07-20
```

The step stays open. Joel still needs to react to the review before anyone writes `## Result`.

## Result (2026-07-21)

Joel reviewed the rendered 2026-07-20 replay (100 real producer messages → 13 decisions: 4 deliver, 2 hold, 6 aggregates covering 93 events, 1 escalate) and approved: "prototype looks gtg." No corrections to voice, aggregation, or hold/deliver judgment were raised — the judgment prompt's spine ("use the smallest interruption that preserves truth") stands as a design input for the production agent.

Iteration path, per the standing call:

- **Hardens in place**: the Claude plugin seed (`prototypes/agent-comms-gateway/claude-plugin/`), the prompt files (identity, vocabulary, judgment), the `readSince(recordedAt, limit, cursor)` replay contract, and the decision-receipt shapes with their every-input-exactly-once validation.
- **Discarded edges**: the journal-spool adapter (replaced when the canonical stream ships its paginated time read) and the review renderer.
- **Next slice**: owned by [Plan the full cutover](./plan-full-cutover.svx) — the prototype proved out, so the plugin seed is the starting point for the production container, not a reference.
